The United States supports the Special Tribunal for Lebanon's trial for four defendants accused of the 2005 assassination of former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri. The US condemns violence as a political tool and calls for all parties to work together to prevent further instability in Lebanon. This includes supporting Lebanese institutions, assisting the Lebanese Armed Forces, and respecting Lebanon's neutrality as agreed in the Baabda Declaration. The US emphasizes the importance of holding accountable those responsible for acts of violence in Lebanon.